      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Response to Conditional (جواب الشرط)",
      "titleArabic": "جواب الشرط",
      "content": [
        "The jawāb al-sharṭ (response clause) follows specific rules depending on the conditional particle used. Sometimes فَ is required to introduce the response."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "With إِنْ: jawāb is majzūm if verb",
        "With لَوْ: jawāb often has لَ prefix",
        "فَ required when jawāb is nominal, imperative, or has certain particles",
        "Jawāb can be a full sentence"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "إِنْ تَأْتِ أُسَاعِدْكَ", "english": "If you come, I will help you (no fā')" },
        { "arabic": "إِنْ جَاءَ فَأَكْرِمْهُ", "english": "If he comes, then honor him (with fā')" }
      ]
    }
